# Commit Approval

- Never run `git commit` without explicit human approval
- Changes are grouped into **logical commit groups** — a group may span multiple repos if they are part of the same logical change
- Before committing a group:
  - Show a summary of all changes in the group, across all repos
  - Show the commit message planned for each repo
  - Wait for the `/approve` command before proceeding
- Only after `/approve` is received, execute all commits in the group
- Each logical group requires its own approval — never batch multiple groups into one approval
